E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ad8232be-923d-42da-a5d7-54974a5945ce%5C%22%3EA%20unique%20new%20species%20of%20sea%20slug%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBathydevius%20typically%20lives%20thousands%20of%20feet%20below%20the%20surface%2C%20far%20from%20the%20coastal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthese-tide-pools-in-hawaii-are-surrounded-by-lava-rocks-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etide%20pools%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20kelp%20forests%20that%20many%20sea%20slugs%20prefer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20captures%20its%20prey%20in%20an%20entirely%20different%20way.%20Usually%2C%20sea%20slugs%20use%20their%20rough%20tongues%20to%20scrape%20food%20off%20the%20seafloor.%20But%20this%20mysterious%2C%20bioluminescent%20mollusk%20uses%20its%20hood%20to%20snatch%20its%20food%20mid-swim.%20Researchers%20still%20aren't%20sure%20how%20these%20slow-moving%20sea%20slugs%20catch%20the%20speedy%20crustaceans%20they%20devour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20unusual%20features%20and%20behaviors%20are%20likely%20the%20result%20of%20its%20unique%20environment%2C%20deep%20below%20the%20surface%20in%20what's%20called%20the%20ocean's%20%26quot%3Bmidnight%20zone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlmost%20every%20aspect%20of%20Bathydevius%20reflects%20an%20adaptation%20to%20this%20habitat%3A%20anatomy%2C%20physiology%2C%20reproduction%2C%20feeding%2C%20behavior%3B%20it's%20unique%2C%26quot%3B%20Robison%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F11%2F12%2Fscience%2Fmystery-mollusk-glowing-sea-slug%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20first%20spotting%20it%20in%20February%202000%2C%20scientists%20exploring%20the%20oceans%20with%20MBARI's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeep-sea-coral-secret-garden-found-scientists-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremotely%20operated%20vehicles%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20come%20across%20it%20over%20150%20times.%20It%20just%20kept%20popping%20up%20from%20Oregon%20to%20Southern%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20no%20one%20knew%20how%20to%20classify%20the%20strange%20sea%20slug.%20Recent%20improvements%20in%20underwater%20cameras%20allowed%20scientists%20to%20film%20its%20vibrant%20bioluminescent%20colors%2C%20and%20genetic%20analysis%20showed%20how%20distant%20it%20is%20from%20other%20sea%20slugs%20on%20the%20family%20tree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20radically%20different%26quot%3B%20from%20its%20relatives%2C%20Robison%20said%2C%20both%20in%20how%20it%20looks%20and%20its%20genetic%20makeup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb63ce1e-6463-423e-847b-6bafe49f8098%5C%22%3EA%20sea%20slug%20in%20the%20midnight%20zone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221603%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bioluminescence%20display%20of%20the%20sea%20slug%20Bathydevius%20caudactylus%20glowing%20green%20in%20dark%20water%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673650ff192f525898589ea4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221078%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20low-light%20camera%20system%20captured%20the%20bioluminescence%20display%20of%20the%20Bathydevius%20caudactylus%20sea%20slug.%3Cp%3E%C2%A9%202021%20MBARI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20trapping%20prey%2C%20the%20slug's%20hood%20can%20snap%20shut%20and%20propel%20the%20animal%20away%20from%20danger.%20Predators%20might%20overlook%20the%20sea%20slug's%20transparent%20body%20or%20be%20startled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F9-bioluminescent-beaches-around-the-world-2016-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eby%20its%20bioluminescence%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20kind%20of%20acts%20as%20a%20burglar%20alarm%2C%26quot%3B%20Robison%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMBARI%20has%20been%20using%20ROVs%20since%20the%20late%201980s.%20It%20now%20uses%20cameras%20that%20can%20film%20bioluminescence%20in%20high%20resolution%2C%20allowing%20researchers%20to%20see