0bevy%20of%20chiefs%20in%20recent%20years.%20Beyond%20the%20usual%20top%20jobs%2C%20some%20organizations%20now%20have%20chief%20experience%20officers%2C%20chief%20AI-ethics%20officers%2C%20and%20chief%20transformation%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20see%20it%20as%20C-suite%20creep.%20Others%20see%20it%20as%20necessary%20diversification%2C%20arguing%20that%20more%20expertise%20than%20ever%20is%20needed%20to%20run%20a%20thriving%20enterprise%20%E2%80%94%20or%20simply%20to%20keep%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeadership%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20rapid%20advances%20in%20tech%2C%20like%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20help%20explain%20why%20CEOs%20might%20want%20to%20pad%20their%20bench.%20But%20some%20suggested%20that%20having%20too%20many%20people%20at%20the%20top%20risked%20muddling%20decision-making%20and%20hurting%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERam%20Charan%2C%20an%20author%20and%20consultant%20who's%20advised%20top%20execs%20and%20boards%20at%20Bank%20of%20America%2C%20Verizon%2C%20and%20Coca-Cola%2C%20said%20that%20many%20C-suites%20had%20grown%20too%20large%20and%20argued%20that%20solving%20big%20problems%20doesn't%20necessarily%20require%20additional%20execs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20need%20more%20people%20at%20the%20top%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20the%20right%20people%20at%20the%20top.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20CEOs%20seem%20to%20think%20the%20ideal%20lieutenants%20are%20those%20in%20roles%20such%20as%20chief%20data%20officer%2C%20chief%20legal%20officer%2C%20and%20chief%20human%20resources%20officer.%20LinkedIn%20said%20in%20September%20that%20those%20were%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomicgraph.linkedin.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fme%2Feconomicgraph%2Fen-us%2FPDF%2Fstate-of-the-c-suite.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efastest-growing%20C-suite%20roles%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20platform%20from%202022%20to%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Saltzman%2C%20director%20of%20growth%20at%20Live%20Data%20Technologies%2C%20said%20a%20review%20of%20its%20figures%20found%20that%2C%20since%202019%2C%20growth%20at%20US%20public%20companies%20in%20newer%20C-suite%20roles%20like%20chief%20customer%20officer%20and%20chief%20corporate%20responsibility%20officer%20has%20been%209.8%25%20faster%20than%20that%20of%20a%20half%20dozen%20traditional%20roles%20like%20CFO%20and%20CMO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharan%20said%20the%20number%20of%20challenges%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20external%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20coming%20at%20companies%20has%20%26quot%3Bgrown%20exponentially%26quot%3B%20from%20about%20a%20decade%20ago.%20These%20include%20AI%20and%20shifts%20in%20how%20companies%20earn%20money%20and%20how%20consumers%20behave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSomebody%20has%20to%20make%20sense%20out%20of%20that%20and%20determine%20priorities%2C%26quot%3B%20Charan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharan%20recommends%20the%20C-suite%20comprise%20a%20handful%20of%20%26quot%3Bbroader-based%26quot%3B%20execs%20who%20can%20think%20critically%20and%20serve%20as%20a%20CEO's%20sounding%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20CEOs%20could%20have%20specialists%2C%20like%20those%20in%20charge%20of%20risk%20management%20report%20to%20them%20even%20if%20they're%20not%20part%20of%20the%20C-suite.%20Still%2C%20he%20said%2C%20there%20shouldn't%20be%20too%20many%20people%2C%20because%20CEOs%20don't%20have%20the%20time%20to%20manage%20that%20many%20direct%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharan's%20recommendations%20might%20seem%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20approaches%20of%20CEOs%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-jensen-huang-ceo-should-have-most-direct-reports-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJensen%20Huang%20at%20Nvidia%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-loses-4-top-executives-ahead-of-robotaxi-event-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%20at%20Tesla%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20are%20said%20to%20have%20dozens%20of%20direct%20reports.%20But%20Charan%20said%20that%20in%20Huang's%20and%20Musk's%20cases%2C%20they%20and%20a%20few%20other%20people%20%26quot%3Bmake%20the%20priority%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EJanet%20Sherlock%2C%20who%20recently%20retired%20as%20the%20chief%20digital%20and%20technology%20officer%20at%20Ralph%20Lauren%20and%20who%20has%20a%20background%20in%20researching%20organizational%20design%2C%20said%20executives%20and%20board%20members%20are%20sometimes%20reluctant%20to%20question%20whether%20a%20person%20in%20a%20top%20management%20position%20has%20the%20skills%20for%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherlock%20gave%20the%20example%20of%20a%20company%20that%20has%20a%20chief%20information%20officer%20but%20then%20hires%20a%20chief%20analytics%20officer%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20hiring%20of%20that%20person%20could%20suggest%20to%20employees%20that%20the%20information%20chief%20%26quot%3Bwasn't%20up%20to%20the%20task.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20Sherlock%20said%2C%20firms%20specializing%20in%20selling%20data%20services%20might%20justifiably%20have%20several%20people%20in%20leadership%20who%20focus%20on%20analytics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20said%20a%20lineup%20that%20includes%20a%20chief%20marketing%20officer%2C%20a%20chief%20information%20officer%2C%20and%20a%20chief%20customer-experience%20officer%20might%20indicate%20insufficient%20internal%20coordination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherlock%20said%20the%20amount%20of%20innovation%20and%20change%20over%20the%20past%2020%20years%20had%20in%20some%20cases%20led%20to%20organizational%20bloat%20at%20the%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20reworking%20and%20rewiring%20organizations%2C%20companies%20have%20often%20thrown%20leaders%20and%20people%20at%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherlock%20speculated%20that%20many%20organizations%20were%20reaching%20a%20%26quot%3Bcritical%20breaking%20point%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20some%20might%20try%20to%20thin%20their%20C-suites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20I%20need%20a%20customer-experience%20officer%20whenever%20I%20have%20a%20chief%20commercial%20officer%2C%20a%20chief%20information%20officer%2C%20and%20a%20chief%20marketing%20officer%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BOr%20are%20the%20processes%20or%20executive%20skill%20sets%20sufficient%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherlock%20said%20that%20in%20the%20research%20she%20completed%20while%20earning%20a%20doctorate%20in%20organizational%20leadership%2C%20she%20found%20that%20overlap%20among%20executives'%20remits%20was%20associated%20with%20worse%20productivity%2C%20product%20quality%2C%20time%20to%20market%2C%20morale%2C%20and%20employee%20engagement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20so%20much%20more%20harmful%20than%20CEOs%2C%20CHROs%2C%20or%20boards%20of%20directors%20are%20aware%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherlock%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that's%20why%20it's%20essential%20to%20maintain%20clear%20responsibilities%20and%20decision-making%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EChristine%20Porath%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20at%20Chapel%20Hill's%20business%20school%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BMastering%20Community%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20collaboration%20among%20C-suite%20executives%20could%20help%20connect%20disciplines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20also%20helps%20role-model%20that%20for%20other%20employees%20and%20the%20organization%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20which%20I%20think%20is%20very%20healthy%2C%26quot%3B%20Porath%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20research%20she%20helped%20conduct%20indicated%20that%20even%20before%20the%20pandemic%20many%20workers%20didn't%20feel%20a%20sense%20of%20community%20at%20work%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20the%20pandemic%20made%20that%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20leaders%20often%20ask%20how%20they%20can%20foster%20greater%20connection%20and%20community%20in%20the%20workplace.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20starts%20at%20the%20top%2C%26quot%3B%20Porath%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPorath%20said%20it%20wouldn't%20do%20any%20good%20to%20just%20slap%20an%20organization's%20values%20on%20a%20website%20or%20an%20office%20wall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20see%20leaders%20living%20them%2C%20people%20tend%20to%20get%20very%20cynical%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20they%20will%20follow%20leaders'%20behavior.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stat%3A%2056%25%20of%20workers%20regularly%20check%20employee%20reviews%20when%20researching%20potential%20employers.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6737b701192f52589858f527%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDorie%20Clark%2C%20a%20communication%20coach%20who%20teaches%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School%20and%20who%20wrote%20%26quot%3BThe%20Long%20Game%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20it's%20understandable%20why%20many%20C-suites%20would%20be%20organized%20with%20clear%20distinctions%20in%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20know%20where%20the%20buck%20stops%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20debate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20chief%20marketing%20officer%2C%20for%20example%2C%20still%20has%20to%20know%20%26quot%3Ban%20incredible%20amount%26quot%3B%20about%20technology%2C%20Clark%20said.%20She%20argued%20that%20a%20C-suite%20should%20have%20those%20clear%20lines%20of%20responsibility%20while%20still%20allowing%20for%20close%20collaboration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20to%20go%20too%20far%2C%20she%20said.%20Clark%20pointed%20to%20organizations%20that%20experimented%20with%20co-CEOs%20%E2%80%94%20a%20setup%20she%20said%20%26quot%3Balmost%20never%20goes%20that%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20lines%20of%20authority%20and%20responsibility%20are%20blurred%2C%20people%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20with%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%20Workers%20don't%20necessarily%20who%20to%20go%20to%2C%20and%20needing%20to%20loop%20in%20more%20people%20can%20slow%20down%20certain%20processes%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20thinks%20the%20C-suite%20has%20bulked%20up%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETy%20Wiggins%2C%20the%20global%20lead%20of%20the%20CEO-%20and%20executive-transitions%20practice%20at%20the%20leadership%20advisory%20firm%20Russell%20Reynolds%20Associates%2C%20said%20that%20as%20tech%20like%20AI%20becomes%20more%20important%20within%20organizations%2C%20bringing%20more%20tech%20experts%20into%20the%20C-suite%20beyond%20chief%20technology%20officers%20or%20chief%20information%20officers%20will%20be%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Russell%20Reynolds%20recommends%20all%20C-suite%20leaders%20become%20proficient%20in%20AI%20and%20other%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWiggins%2C%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20New%20CEO%2C%26quot%3B%20argued%20that%20leaders%20needed%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bcloser%20connections%26quot%3B%20to%20different%20aspects%20of%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20realize%20when%20you're%20a%20CEO%20that%20the%20information%20coming%20to%20you%20is%20filtered%20multiple%20times%20before%20it%20gets%20to%20your%20desk%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWiggins%20said%20most%20CEOs'%20remits%20had%20expanded%20over%20the%20past%2015%20years%20%E2%80%94%20they%20often%20now%20include%20digital%20transformation%2C%20employee%20well-being%2C%20sustainability%2C%20and%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20efforts%2C%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWiggins%20said%20that's%20why%20there's%20more%20pressure%20on%20C-suite%20leaders%20to%20act%20as%20a%20well-informed%20unit%20of%20experts%20rather%20than%20technical%20specialists.%20That%20can%20mean%20extra%20work%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3