pe.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPast%20presidents%20have%20created%20commissions%20with%20the%20same%20goals%2C%20and%20they've%20had%20mixed%20results.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETrump%20may%20find%20it%20easier%20than%20Reagan%20or%20Clinton%20to%20get%20Congress%20to%20take%20action.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EElon%20Musk%20and%20Vivek%20Ramaswamy%20are%20promising%20to%20tame%20the%20federal%20government.%20They%20aren't%20the%20first.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20unlike%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%20and%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%3Cspan%3E%2C%20who%20both%20largely%20failed%20attempts%20at%20taming%20federal%20spending%20and%20sprawl%2C%20their%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20has%20a%20crucial%20advantage%3A%20Republican%20control%20of%20both%20chambers%20of%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20political%20reality%20opens%20up%20more%20avenues%20to%20achieving%20their%20ambitious%20goal%20of%20cutting%20%242%20trillion%20in%20spending.%20Budget%20reconciliation%2C%20a%20process%20whereby%20spending%20and%20tax%20bills%20can%20bypass%20the%20usual%20filibuster%20rules%2C%20could%20need%20just%2051%20Senate%20votes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Republicans%20are%20projected%20to%20hold%2052%20seats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20its%20name%2C%20Musk%20and%20Ramaswamy's%20panel%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%2C%20won't%20be%20a%20government%20department.%20Substantial%20changes%20to%20the%20federal%20budget%20would%20most%20likely%20require%20action%20from%20legislators%2C%20though%20Trump%20transition%20officials%20are%20reportedly%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2024%2F11%2F13%2Felon-musk-government-efficiency-congress-budget-law%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eshort-circuit%20Congress'%20power%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20over%20spending.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20two%20men%20appear%20to%20be%20well%20positioned%20to%20advise%20Trump%20on%20how%20to%20make%20the%20deepest%20cuts%20to%20the%20federal%20government%20in%20generations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f17bde88-48d2-4aed-ae9d-cead1ffcb9b5%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPast%20presidents%20have%20tried%20to%20cut%20the%20federal%20budget%20with%20mixed%20success%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20federal%20government%20isn't%20a%20business.%20Decisions%20about%20which%20agencies%20get%20which%20money%20for%20which%20purpose%20and%20how%20the%20money%20is%20raised%20are%20hashed%20out%20in%20Congress.%20Lacking%20the%20awesome%20power%20of%20a%20corporate%20CEO%2C%20past%20presidents%2C%20including%20Ronald%20Reagan%20and%20Bill%20Clinton%2C%20have%20struggled%20to%20tame%20the%20beast.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20lot%20more%20restrictions%20on%20what%20you%20can%20and%20can't%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20David%20Walker%2C%20a%20fiscal%20watchdog%20who%20led%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20from%201998%20through%202008.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20cultural%20barriers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201982%2C%20Reagan%20tasked%20J.%20Peter%20Grace%2C%20a%20chemicals%20executive%2C%20with%20creating%20a%20team%20of%20private-sector%20%26quot%3Bbloodhounds%26quot%3B%20to%20root%20through%20the%20government%2C%20looking%20for%20waste%20and%20inefficiency.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20his%20crew%20of%20about%20160%20senior%20corporate%20executives%2C%20later%20known%20as%20the%20Grace%20Commission%2C%20published%20over%202%2C000%20recommendations%20they%20said%20would%20save%20more%20than%20%24424%20billion%20over%20three%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government's%20in-house%20budget%20experts%2C%20however%2C%20didn't%20think%20the%20changes%20would%20be%20as%20impactful%20as%20the%20Grace%20Commission%20did.%20Most%20of%20the%20proposals%20required%20acts%20of%20Congress%20that%20never%20materialized.%20Some%20changes%2C%20like%20improving%20the%20government's%20debt-collection%20efforts%20and%20reducing%20head%20count%20among%20certain%20groups%20of%20federal%20employees%2C%20were%20made%20by%20the%20executive%20branch%2C%20bypassing%20Democrats%20in%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20nonprofit%20Citizens%20Against%20Government%20Waste%2C%20which%20carried%20on%20the%20mission%20of%20the%20Grace%20Commission%2C%20said%20last%20year%20that%20the%20US%20government%20had%20cut%20spending%20by%20a%20cumulative%20total%20of%20%242.4%20trillion%20since%20the%201980s%20by%20implementing%20recommendations%20from%20the%20Grace%20Commission%20and%20from%20the%20nonprofit%20itself.%20Musk%20has%20claimed%20his%20committee%20could%20cut%20nearly%20that%20much%20spending%20in%20one%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClinton%20took%20another%20stab%20at%20cutting%20federal%20spending%20and%20improving%20government%20processes%20with%20his%20National%20Performance%20Review%2C%20which%20was%20led%20and%20staffed%20by%20federal%20employees%20instead%20of%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20initiative%20succeeded%20in%20shrinking%20the%20federal%20workforce%20by%20more%20than%20300%2C000%20workers%20during%20Clinton's%20term%2C%20though%20the%20groundwork%20for%20some%20of%20those%20reductions%20was%20laid%20under%20Reagan.%20But%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgovinfo.library.unt.edu%2Fnpr%2Flibrary%2Fpapers%2Fbkgrd%2Fbrief.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eonly%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20its%20proposals%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20required%20legislative%20action%20managed%20to%20clear%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201999%2C%20the%20Clinton%20administration%20claimed%20that%20it%20had%20saved%20%24137%20billion.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fassets%2Fggd-99-120.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGovernment%20Accountability%20Office%20said%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20figure%20included%20some%20double%20counting%20and%20nearly%20%2425%20billion%20that%20was%20merely%20%26quot%3Bconsistent%20with%26quot%3B%20the%20initiative's%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Breinventing%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMusk%20and%20Trump's%20efforts%20could%20go%20further.%20Trump%20said%20the%20DOGE%20commission%20would%20have%20until%20July%204%2C%202026%2C%20to%20deliver%20a%20plan%2C%20but%20Musk%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%20that%20it%20would%20%26quot%3Bbe%20done%20much%20faster.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294b4d06c-a556-4a4b-879d-8a7ebc8faa8b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat's%20different%20this%20time%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAny%20proposals%20from%20Musk%20and%20Ramaswamy%20that%20Trump%20accepts%20would%20have%20a%20much%20better%20chance%20of%20getting%20through%20Congress%20than%20those%20from%20Reagan's%20or%20Clinton's%20commissions%20because%20Republicans%20are%20on%20track%20to%20control%20both%20chambers%20of%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReagan's%20and%20Clinton's%20commissions%20came%20up%20against%20a%20Congress%20at%20least%20partly%20controlled%20by%20the%20other%20party.%20While%20contentious%20bills%20often%20can't%20clear%20the%20Senate%20because%2060%20votes%20are%20required%20to%20overcome%20the%20filibuster%2C%20many%20spending-related%20proposals%20can%20pass%20with%20a%2051-vote%20majority%20through%20a%20process%20called%20budget%20reconciliation.%20Republicans%20are%20set%20to%20hold%2052%20seats%20starting%20next%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThomas%20Schatz%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Citizens%20Against%20Government%20Waste%2C%20said%20Trump%20would%20likely%20have%20at%20least%20two%20opportunities%20to%20pass%20a%20budget%20through%20reconciliation.%20The%20fact%20that%20Musk%20and%20Ramaswamy%20will%20have%20had%20a%20two-month%20head%20start%20before%20Trump%20is%20sworn%20in%20also%20helps%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20government-efficiency%20effort%20%26quot%3Bcan%20be%20set%20up%20faster%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20depends%20on%20how%20many%20members%20the%20president%20would%20like%20on%20the%20commission%2C%20and%20I%20have%20no%20idea.%20They%20haven't%20asked%20me.%20My%20suggestion%20is%20to%20keep%20it%20smaller.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20Musk%20has%20said%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%20which%20has%20sued%20him%20twice%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bbroken%26quot%3B%20and%20accused%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20of%20delaying%20SpaceX%20launches%20with%20%26quot%3Bkafkaesque%20paperwork.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20recent%20posts%20on%20X%2C%20he%20has%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20rewarding%20government%20employees%20who%20spend%20wisely%20and%20firing%20those%20who%20waste%20money.%20Congress%20hasn't%20figured%20in%20recent%20posts%2C%20though%20in%202022%20Musk%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1589714533345812480%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etweeted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20he%20preferred%20when%20the%20presidency%20and%20Congress%20were%20controlled%20by%20different%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20September%20appearance%20on%20Lex%20Fridman's%20podcast%2C%20Ramaswamy%20outlined%20a%20thought%20experiment%20for%20shrinking%20the%20federal%20workforce%3A%20Fire%20all%20nonelected%20federal%20workers%20whose%20Social%20Security%20numbers%20end%20in%20odd%20numbers%2C%20then%20fire%20half%20of%20the%20remaining%20employees%2C%20those%20whose%20numbers%20start%20with%20odd%20digits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20argued%20that%20this%20arbitrary%2075%25%20reduction%20%E2%80%94%20about%202.2%20million%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20would%20avoid%20discrimination%20lawsuits%20while%20barely%20affecting%20government%20services.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVeronique%20de%20Rugy%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20libertarian%20think%20tank%20Mercatus%20Center%2C%20has%20said%20Musk%20and%20Ramaswamy%20could%20save%20%242%20trillion%20if%20they%20embraced%20what%20many%20other%20economists%20would%20consider%20radical%20reforms.%20She%20said%20that%20ending%20aid%20to%20states%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20Cato%20Institute%20estimated%20amounted%20to%20%24697%20billion%20in%202018%20and%20%24721%20billion%20in%202019%20%E2%80%94%20could%20go%20a%20long%20way%2C%20as%20could%20hacking%20away%20at%20corporate%20welfare%20for%20sectors%20like%20pharmaceuticals%20and%20electric%20cars.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20she%20also%20expressed%20skepticism%20about%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20ability%20to%20build%20the%20bridges%20that%20could%20be%20necessary%20for%20big%20changes.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20going%20to%20piss%20off%20everyone%20for%20stupid%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20also%20third%20rails%20of%20political%20spending%20that%20some%20are%20doubtful%20Trump%20will%20be%20able%20or%20eager%20to%20tackle%2C%20even%20if%20Musk%20and%20Ramaswamy%20advised%20him%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESocial%20Security%20and%20Medicare%20are%20the%20two%20single%20biggest%20areas%20of%20federal%20spending%2C%20and%20changing%20them%20could%20be%20politically%20unpopular.%20Trump%20has%20generally%20said%20he%20won't%20touch%20them%20%E2%80%94%20except%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tax-cuts-social-security-boomers-benefit-fund-depletion-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eeliminating%20taxes%20on%20Social%20Security%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20payments%2C%20which%20would%20mean%20fewer%20benefits%20for%20retirees%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarmarks%2C%20which%20allow%20members%20of%20Congress%20to%20send%20money%20back%20to%20their%20home%20districts%20and%20states%2C%20are%20another%20significant%20source%20of%20federal%20waste%2C%20and%20even%20a%20GOP-led%20House%20and%20Senate%20may%20be%20leery%20of%20getting%20rid%20of%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20incentive%20in%20politics%20is%20to%20make%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20de%20Rugy%20said.%20Everyone%2C%20she%20added%2C%20likes%20a%20ribbon-cutting%20ceremony.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-elon-musk-cutting-federal-spending-could-work-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731696204000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67350a43fa0140cdd5632e83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-elon-musk-cutting-federal-spending-could-work-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There's%20a%20chance%20the%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency's%20plans%20could%20lead%20to%20the%20deepest%20cuts%20to%20the%20federal%20government%20in%20generations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jnewsham%40insider.com%20(Jack%20Newsham)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A65%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-elon-musk-cutting-federal-spending-could-work-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fusion%20Entertainment%20Signs%20Documentary%20Filmmaker%20and%20%E2%80%98The%20Easy%20Kind%E2%80%99%20Director%20Katy%20Chevigny%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731696055000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FKaty-Chevigny-Headshot-2024.jpeg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D